Travellers long night at weighbridge gridlock             Antony Gitonga  04th Aug 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 Antony Gitonga  04th Aug 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 Antony Gitonga   An endless queue of trucks at the Gilgil weighbridge on the Nairobi-Nakuru highway yesterday. Hundreds of travellers were caught up in a traffic snarl-up that extended 10km on both directions of the weighbridge on Friday night. [Antony Gitonga, Standard]  An endless queue of trucks at the Gilgil weighbridge on the Nairobi-Nakuru highway yesterday. Hundreds of travellers were caught up in a traffic snarl-up that extended 10km on both directions of the weighbridge on Friday night. [Antony Gitonga, Standard] An endless queue of trucks at the Gilgil weighbridge on the Nairobi-Nakuru highway yesterday. Hundreds of travellers were caught up in a traffic snarl-up that extended 10km on both directions of the weighbridge on Friday night. [Antony Gitonga, Standard] An endless queue of trucks at the Gilgil weighbridge on the Nairobi-Nakuru highway yesterday. Hundreds of travellers were caught up in a traffic snarl-up that extended 10km on both directions of the weighbridge on Friday night. [Antony Gitonga, Standard]      SEE ALSO :Four traders killed by speeding lorry in Naivasha SEE ALSO : Four traders killed by speeding lorry in Naivasha   Heavy trucks    SEE ALSO :Nairobi-Nakuru highway hit by mad traffic since Friday [PHOTOS] SEE ALSO : Nairobi-Nakuru highway hit by mad traffic since Friday [PHOTOS]         Worst days     We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. HERE Related Topics Nairobi-Nakuru highway Gilgil weighbridge Traffic Jam